The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 February is 208,944 (24,082 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 02 February, there were 10,674 new confirmed cases (1,230.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 26 January, there were 11,071 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 4% (397 fewer cases).
